{
    "name": "Gibtas Spawn Swarm",
    "type": "creature",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Gibtas Spawn Swarm",
            "type": "section",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Pathfinder #164: Hands of the Devil",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Pathfinder #164: Hands of the Devil pg. 80",
                        "alt": "Pathfinder #164: Hands of the Devil pg. 80",
                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq024ur"
                    },
                    "page": 80
                }
            ],
            "html": "When a gibtas gorges itself on an incredible amount of flesh, it vomits up a pool of acid filled with tiny pink egg sacs that burst immediately. The new babies hunt as a pack, growing in size until they go their separate ways or consume each other.<br/><br/><b><u><a aonid=\"5\" game-obj=\"Skills\" general=\"true\">Recall Knowledge - Aberration</a></u> (<u><a aonid=\"11\" game-obj=\"Skills\">Occultism</a></u>)</b>: DC 24"
        },
        {
            "name": "Gibtas",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "name": "Gibtas Companions",
                    "type": "section",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Pathfinder #164: Hands of the Devil",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Pathfinder #164: Hands of the Devil pg. 80",
                                "alt": "Pathfinder #164: Hands of the Devil pg. 80",
                                "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq024ur"
                            },
                            "page": 80
                        }
                    ],
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "advice_and_rules",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Advice and Rules",
                    "image": {
                        "type": "image",
                        "name": "Advice and Rules",
                        "image": "Sidebar_1_AdviceAndRules.png"
                    },
                    "html": "A gibtas can make for an unusual animal companion, with the GM's permission. Use the statistics for a <a aonid=\"1\" game-obj=\"AnimalCompanions\">bear animal companion</a>, except the companion has the rare trait, is an <a aonid=\"1\" game-obj=\"Traits\">aberration</a> rather than an <a aonid=\"9\" game-obj=\"Traits\">animal</a>, has <a aonid=\"12\" game-obj=\"MonsterAbilities\">darkvision</a> rather than <a aonid=\"23\" game-obj=\"MonsterAbilities\">low-light vision</a>, and gains the <a aonid=\"1045\" game-obj=\"Monsters\">gibtas bounder's</a> Bouncing Slam as an advanced maneuver instead of <a aonid=\"15\" game-obj=\"Actions\">Bear Hug</a>."
                },
                {
                    "name": "Wild Gibtases",
                    "type": "section",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Pathfinder #164: Hands of the Devil",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Pathfinder #164: Hands of the Devil pg. 80",
                                "alt": "Pathfinder #164: Hands of the Devil pg. 80",
                                "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq024ur"
                            },
                            "page": 80
                        }
                    ],
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "additional_lore",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
                    "image": {
                        "type": "image",
                        "name": "Additional Lore",
                        "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png"
                    },
                    "html": "In the wild, gibtases are scavenger creatures, avoiding much larger and more powerful predators while feeding off abandoned scraps. This limits their consumption-based reproduction. By spawning hundreds of offspring at once during times of plentiful food, they ensure the propagation of their species only during times of plenty."
                }
            ],
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Pathfinder #164: Hands of the Devil",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Pathfinder #164: Hands of the Devil pg. 80",
                        "alt": "Pathfinder #164: Hands of the Devil pg. 80",
                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq024ur"
                    },
                    "page": 80
                }
            ],
            "html": "This rubbery, spheroid scavenger is nearly all acid-dripping mouth, with five bulbous black eyes and two powerful, gangly legs. A gibtas often forms a bond with a single other creature\u2014usually, a more powerful <a aonid=\"1\" game-obj=\"Traits\">aberration</a>\u2014 and serves this master loyally, if erratically. Creatures who keep a gibtas as a pet or guard soon learn to keep it away from any important possessions they don't want spattered with acid."
        }
    ],
